<learningAssessment xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="learningAssessment-2797" domains="(topic hi-d)                             (topic ut-d)                             (topic indexing-d)                            (topic learningInteractionBase-d)                            (topic learningInteractionBase-d learning-d)                            (topic learningmeta-d)                            (topic learningBase+learningInteractionBase-d)                            (topic learningBase+learningInteractionBase-d learningAssessment)   " ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" class="- topic/topic learningBase/learningBase     learningAssessment/learningAssessment "><title class="- topic/title ">Quiz 1</title><shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc "/><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><author type="creator" href="http://www.easydita.com" scope="external" format="html" class="- topic/author ">Mike Rice</author><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><keywords class="- topic/keywords "/></metadata></prolog><learningAssessmentbody class="- topic/body  learningBase/learningBasebody learningAssessment/learningAssessmentbody "><lcInteraction class="- topic/section learningBase/lcInteraction "><lcTrueFalse id="tf1" class="+ topic/fig learningInteractionBase-d/lcInteractionBase learning-d/lcTrueFalse "><lcQuestion class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/lcQuestionBase learning-d/lcQuestion ">Conref is an element that is valid anywhere in a DITA topic.</lcQuestion><lcAnswerOptionGroup class="+ topic/ul learningInteractionBase-d/ul learning-d/lcAnswerOptionGroup "><lcAnswerOption class="+ topic/li learningInteractionBase-d/li learning-d/lcAnswerOption "><lcAnswerContent class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcAnswerContent ">True</lcAnswerContent></lcAnswerOption><lcAnswerOption class="+ topic/li learningInteractionBase-d/li learning-d/lcAnswerOption "><lcAnswerContent class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcAnswerContent ">False</lcAnswerContent></lcAnswerOption></lcAnswerOptionGroup><lcFeedbackIncorrect class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcFeedbackIncorrect ">The conref <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">attribute</i> of the referencing element holds a reference to the reused element’s id. Any element can have a conref attribute.</lcFeedbackIncorrect><lcFeedbackCorrect class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcFeedbackCorrect ">That’s right. Conref is not an element. It is an attribute of an element.</lcFeedbackCorrect></lcTrueFalse><lcSingleSelect id="ss1" class="+ topic/fig learningInteractionBase-d/lcInteractionBase learning-d/lcSingleSelect "><lcQuestion class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/lcQuestionBase learning-d/lcQuestion ">In the following conref example, which is the id of the referencing element?</lcQuestion><lcAsset class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcAsset "><image placement="inline" href="../media/conref-sample-1.png" class="- topic/image "/></lcAsset><lcAnswerOptionGroup class="+ topic/ul learningInteractionBase-d/ul learning-d/lcAnswerOptionGroup "><lcAnswerOption class="+ topic/li learningInteractionBase-d/li learning-d/lcAnswerOption "><lcAnswerContent class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcAnswerContent ">fruit</lcAnswerContent><lcCorrectResponse name="lcCorrectResponse" value="lcCorrectResponse" class="+ topic/data learningInteractionBase-d/data learning-d/lcCorrectResponse "/></lcAnswerOption><lcAnswerOption class="+ topic/li learningInteractionBase-d/li learning-d/lcAnswerOption "><lcAnswerContent class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcAnswerContent ">pear</lcAnswerContent></lcAnswerOption><lcAnswerOption class="+ topic/li learningInteractionBase-d/li learning-d/lcAnswerOption "><lcAnswerContent class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcAnswerContent ">fruitnotes</lcAnswerContent></lcAnswerOption><lcAnswerOption class="+ topic/li learningInteractionBase-d/li learning-d/lcAnswerOption "><lcAnswerContent class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcAnswerContent ">fruittopic</lcAnswerContent></lcAnswerOption></lcAnswerOptionGroup><lcFeedbackIncorrect class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcFeedbackIncorrect "> The referencing element is in the topic with the id fruitttopic. But that topic is not specifically the referencing element. The actual referencing element - the one making the content reference - is the &lt;note&gt; element that has the conref attribute. Its id is fruit.</lcFeedbackIncorrect><lcFeedbackCorrect class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcFeedbackCorrect ">Right. The referencing element, the element making the content reference, is the one with the conref attribute. The the referenced element is the conref target - the element indicated in the conref attribute. </lcFeedbackCorrect></lcSingleSelect><lcTrueFalse id="tf2" class="+ topic/fig learningInteractionBase-d/lcInteractionBase learning-d/lcTrueFalse "><lcQuestion class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/lcQuestionBase learning-d/lcQuestion ">An id is required for the referenced element of a conref.</lcQuestion><lcAnswerOptionGroup class="+ topic/ul learningInteractionBase-d/ul learning-d/lcAnswerOptionGroup "><lcAnswerOption class="+ topic/li learningInteractionBase-d/li learning-d/lcAnswerOption "><lcAnswerContent class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcAnswerContent ">True</lcAnswerContent><lcCorrectResponse name="lcCorrectResponse" value="lcCorrectResponse" class="+ topic/data learningInteractionBase-d/data learning-d/lcCorrectResponse "/></lcAnswerOption><lcAnswerOption class="+ topic/li learningInteractionBase-d/li learning-d/lcAnswerOption "><lcAnswerContent class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcAnswerContent ">False</lcAnswerContent></lcAnswerOption></lcAnswerOptionGroup><lcFeedbackIncorrect class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcFeedbackIncorrect ">A conref refers to a specific occurrence of an element. An id is required so that there is no ambiguity when there is more than one of the same kind of element.</lcFeedbackIncorrect><lcFeedbackCorrect class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcFeedbackCorrect ">Yes. A conref refers to a specific occurrence of an element. Requiring an id means that there is no ambiguity when there is more than one of the same kind of element.</lcFeedbackCorrect></lcTrueFalse><lcTrueFalse id="tf3" class="+ topic/fig learningInteractionBase-d/lcInteractionBase learning-d/lcTrueFalse "><lcQuestion class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/lcQuestionBase learning-d/lcQuestion ">An id is required for the referencing element of a conref.</lcQuestion><lcAnswerOptionGroup class="+ topic/ul learningInteractionBase-d/ul learning-d/lcAnswerOptionGroup "><lcAnswerOption class="+ topic/li learningInteractionBase-d/li learning-d/lcAnswerOption "><lcAnswerContent class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcAnswerContent ">True</lcAnswerContent></lcAnswerOption><lcAnswerOption class="+ topic/li learningInteractionBase-d/li learning-d/lcAnswerOption "><lcAnswerContent class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcAnswerContent ">False</lcAnswerContent><lcCorrectResponse name="lcCorrectResponse" value="lcCorrectResponse" class="+ topic/data learningInteractionBase-d/data learning-d/lcCorrectResponse "/></lcAnswerOption></lcAnswerOptionGroup><lcFeedbackIncorrect class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcFeedbackIncorrect ">The referencing element doesn’t require an id. The referenced element does, though.</lcFeedbackIncorrect><lcFeedbackCorrect class="+ topic/p learningInteractionBase-d/p learning-d/lcFeedbackCorrect ">Right. The referenced element does require an id, though.</lcFeedbackCorrect></lcTrueFalse></lcInteraction></learningAssessmentbody></learningAssessment>
